oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Benjamin Banneker
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Benjamin Banneker assisting with the plans for laying out Washington, D.C.
Benjamin Banneker was a free African-American surveyor, naturalist, and farmer. He was part of the group that surveyed the original boundaries of the District of Columbia.
